My family and I were in DC over Christmas.  Got back to hotel one night starving of course, and decided to order pizza.  Lots of choices in DC, but found this place on yelp and decided to give them a try.  Pizza arrived after a reasonable amount of time, but one pizza was missing.  I had already paid over $60 for this order.  The driver called the shop, and the gentleman tried to tell me I didn't order an additional pizza.  I said I did, and had the charge on card to prove it.  He said, he'd refund the whole amount and apologized for the confusion.  I thought this was too generous on their part, but he insisted.  After a month, no refund had been authorized.  I contacted them multiple times over several weeks, and was assured that they were working on it.  I uploaded a picture of my receipt showing the charge.  It's been 2.5 months now, and nobody has ever contacted me.  This is my first negative review, and I feel like I've given them every opportunity to make it right.  You might dine in with them, but I'd never order a pizza delivered unless you like to be charged double and still have to leave the hotel to feed one of your kids.
